{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/adapters/fs.rs:3040-3058` deliberately stops backfilling `plan_hash` when a new `TaskRunEntry` is created, and `src/adapters/fs.rs:2583-2622` only backfills existing rows when `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation` matches the current snapshot, skipping every `snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation == None` row. That leaves Issue 3 unimplemented: callers that omit `plan_hash` still produce `TaskRunEntry { plan_hash: None }` for new starts and for many existing/open rows, even though the accepted contract requires adapter-level snapshot backfill in both cases. The updated tests in `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:4727-4817`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:5274-5285`, and `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:5635-5844` now assert the opposite behavior, so the regression is masked instead of covered.","rationale":"Lineage remains incomplete whenever callers omit `plan_hash`, so the task's acceptance criteria still fail and downstream repair/reporting paths continue to lose the canonical plan version."},{"body":"In `src/adapters/fs.rs:3118-3176`, the `run_id` update path returns an error as soon as it sees a single open runless row whose `started_at` differs from the request. That means a replay of an older completed runless attempt is still rejected once a newer retry has started: the code never falls through to the terminal replay matcher at `src/adapters/fs.rs:3127-3152`, even if a completed row exists with the requested `started_at`. The accepted Issue 2 fix requires started-at-based disambiguation for terminal replays too; this branch still breaks the partial-write repair path described in `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:527-530`.","rationale":"After a later retry begins, you can no longer repair metadata/journal state for the earlier completed runless attempt, so lineage and journal recovery stop being idempotent."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone-lineage changes across the current task. Journal-detail struct deduplication and the new started_at guards are mostly in the right direction, but I found two correctness gaps: plan_hash auto-population is still intentionally disabled contrary to the accepted Issue 3 contract, and named terminal replays still fail if a newer runless retry is open."}